        "content": "<p>i find myself using racket's varadic fold a lot. it looks like <code>List.foldl</code> takes strictly one list, however. I suspect the answer is \"use <code>List.zip</code>\" - but does there happen to exist a fold that can take in an arbitrary number of lists, like so?</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Racket\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nb\">foldl</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"k\">Î»</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">acc</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nb\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">acc</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nb\">abs</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nb\">-</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"p\">))))</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nb\">sort</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">l1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">&lt;</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nb\">sort</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">l2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">&lt;</span><span class=\"p\">))</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
